messages.content: Are you out of the house yet?
All right, get out of the house.
We can't. There's nothing open. If I open the door, it's too much smoke.
Okay. All right. What's your name?
All right. Try to get out of the house if you can.
Yes. Okay. I'm going to stay on the phone with you, all right?
Okay, honey, are you on the first floor or second floor? Where in the house are you?
Okay, if I'm looking at your house, are you on the left or the right side?
I'm all the way at the top.
You're all the way at the top?
Okay, you're on the second floor. If I come up your stairs, which way do I turn to get to you?
I'm in the room that has the door closed.
You're in the room that has the door closed? All the other rooms have doors open?
Okay, can you get to a window and open it?
Can you see if it's the front of the house or the back of the house?
I'm in the back. I'm on the side of the house.
Which side? If I'm looking at your house, is it the right or the left side?
Ma'am, how many people are in the room?
One, two, three, four, five. We have five people in the room.
